Charlie's parents instructed me
to say these words to you.

35:37.903 --> 35:39.903
As they crossed
Lindell Boulevard,

35:39.905 --> 35:41.238
Mom and Dad didn't notice

35:41.240 --> 35:43.473
that Charlie had stopped
to pet a dog.

35:43.475 --> 35:45.909
The dog was also named Charlie.

35:45.911 --> 35:47.777
Actually,
- That's a nice touch, but...

35:47.779 --> 35:49.613
When they noticed that
Charlie... their Charlie...

35:49.615 --> 35:53.183
wasn't with them,
their heart stopped.

35:53.185 --> 35:54.217
The light had just changed,

35:54.219 --> 35:57.454
and cars were about to zoom
through the crosswalk.

35:57.456 --> 35:58.822
But when they turned around,

35:58.824 --> 36:02.826
Charlie was patiently waiting
at the other side...

36:02.828 --> 36:04.261
because he knew the rules.

36:04.263 --> 36:07.531
Red hand... stop.
Man walking... go.

36:07.533 --> 36:09.799
I don't want to hear anymore.

36:09.801 --> 36:12.702
They want you
to hear everything.

36:12.704 --> 36:14.571
The signal changed,

36:14.573 --> 36:16.740
"Go," said the walking man.

36:16.742 --> 36:19.643
So Charlie ran to his parents.

36:19.645 --> 36:23.213
And you gunned it
through that red light...

36:23.215 --> 36:24.548
at 70 miles an hour

36:24.550 --> 36:27.984
to go wherever the hell
you were going.

36:27.986 --> 36:29.586
And you killed Charlie.

36:29.588 --> 36:31.254
No. It was an accident.

36:31.256 --> 36:34.591
Yeah. Accidents happen.

36:34.593 --> 36:37.394
But this was different.
No, it wasn't.

36:37.396 --> 36:38.328
This was different.

36:38.330 --> 36:42.799
In an accident, the right thing
for a person to do is to stop

36:42.801 --> 36:44.968
and take responsibility
for what they did,

36:44.970 --> 36:48.672
especially if they killed
another human being,

36:48.674 --> 36:51.641
especially if they killed
a child.

36:51.643 --> 36:53.009
I want to talk to a lawyer.
I want to talk...

36:53.011 --> 36:56.980
You should've done that
a long time ago, Bill.

36:56.982 --> 36:59.115
So now you're talking to me.

36:59.117 --> 37:03.453
♪ Blue days, all of them gone ♪

37:03.455 --> 37:05.388
Not for her!

37:05.390 --> 37:10.727
♪ Nothing but blue skies
from now on ♪

37:10.729 --> 37:11.461
[ Laughter ]

37:11.463 --> 37:13.797
Charlie's parents looked
for this monster

37:13.799 --> 37:15.265
who took their child from them,

37:15.267 --> 37:17.434
who ruined their lives
eight years ago today.

37:17.436 --> 37:18.935
And they don't want to endure
the thought of you

37:18.937 --> 37:21.938
living one day longer than
their son was on this earth.

37:21.940 --> 37:24.407
I'm really sorry.
I really am.

37:24.409 --> 37:28.612
That's what people always say
in these moments.

37:28.614 --> 37:30.647
But it isn't true, Bill.

37:30.649 --> 37:35.318
What you really are is scared.

37:35.320 --> 37:36.920
Don't be.

37:36.922 --> 37:40.824
It will be quick.
- What?

37:40.826 --> 37:43.893
You're gonna have
a heart attack.

37:43.895 --> 37:46.029
Shh, shh, shh, shh.

37:46.031 --> 37:49.966
So no one
will ever know the truth.

37:49.968 --> 37:54.371
You don't get the dignity
of the truth.

37:54.373 --> 37:58.375
Only Charlie's parents
will know.

37:58.377 --> 38:02.479
And me. And you.

38:02.680 --> 38:04.881
Don't try to run.

38:11.822 --> 38:13.657
Can we go a little faster?

38:13.659 --> 38:15.025
[ Band increases tempo ] Yes.

38:15.027 --> 38:19.696
♪ Blue skies smilin' at me ♪

38:19.698 --> 38:26.169
♪ Nothin' but blue skies
do I see ♪

38:26.171 --> 38:29.539
♪ Never saw the sun
shinin' so bright ♪

38:29.541 --> 38:32.208
♪ Never saw things
goin' so right ♪

38:32.210 --> 38:35.445
♪ Noticing the days
hurrying by ♪

38:35.447 --> 38:37.013
♪ When you're in love ♪

38:37.015 --> 38:40.684
♪ My, how they fly ♪

38:40.686 --> 38:42.052
Oh, key change!

38:42.054 --> 38:45.455
♪ Blue days, all of them gone ♪

38:45.457 --> 38:46.089
Whoo!

38:46.091 --> 38:52.929
♪ Nothin' but blue skies
from now on ♪

38:52.931 --> 38:56.599
Whoo!
[ Music stops ]

39:01.072 --> 39:02.539
No, but you...
you are just

39:02.541 --> 39:05.475
a total Renaissance woman.

39:05.477 --> 39:08.345
You write.
You sing.

39:08.347 --> 39:11.014
You have a hot Spanish husband.

39:11.016 --> 39:12.048
I can't stand the guy.

39:12.050 --> 39:13.149
What?
Don't say that.

39:13.151 --> 39:15.085
Well, you don't like
your husband, either.

39:15.087 --> 39:17.954
The first words you used
to describe him were "fat"

39:17.956 --> 39:19.489
and "uninteresting."

39:19.491 --> 39:23.493
You have some dude's
number in your wallet.

39:23.495 --> 39:28.064
That is this college kid
from the car wash.

39:28.066 --> 39:30.166
I've kept it for three years.

39:30.168 --> 39:31.134
Shit.
- I know.

39:31.136 --> 39:33.536
I know. I know.
I'm ridiculous.

39:33.538 --> 39:34.371
Completely.

39:34.373 --> 39:36.706
You're fantasizing about
walking out of the hotel,

39:36.708 --> 39:40.910
running away,
- Instead of just doing it.

39:42.680 --> 39:45.715
I can't.

39:45.717 --> 39:47.117
Listen, don't cry.
I-I'm just...

39:47.119 --> 39:50.520
No. I mean, you're right,
obviously,

39:50.522 --> 39:52.155
but...

39:52.157 --> 39:54.491
I can't.

39:54.493 --> 39:57.427
Why not?

39:57.429 --> 39:58.728
I can't talk about it.

39:58.730 --> 40:00.363
Yes, you can.
- You're just choosing not to.

40:00.365 --> 40:04.200
I mean I'm not<i> allowed</i>
to talk about it.

40:04.202 --> 40:05.435
Says who?

40:05.437 --> 40:07.570
Says Bill.

40:09.673 --> 40:13.343
Eight years ago,
he ran over a little boy

40:13.345 --> 40:15.478
and he killed him.

40:15.480 --> 40:17.680
What?

40:17.682 --> 40:18.715
And...

40:18.717 --> 40:22.652
And I was in the passenger seat.

40:22.654 --> 40:25.288
Bill made me swear

40:25.290 --> 40:28.391
that I would never tell anyone,

40:28.393 --> 40:31.661
and I haven't.

40:31.663 --> 40:33.663
I'm horrible.

40:35.666 --> 40:37.600
So, every year,
on the anniversary,

40:37.602 --> 40:38.668
we take a trip,

40:38.670 --> 40:42.172
you know, just pretend
like it didn't happen.

40:42.174 --> 40:45.041
And I just thought
- It would eventually go away,

40:45.043 --> 40:47.277
but it just doesn't.

40:47.279 --> 40:49.712
We just get more and more...

40:49.714 --> 40:52.449
horrible to each other.

40:54.185 --> 40:57.153
I hate him.

40:59.457 --> 41:00.790
That's marriage, right?

41:00.792 --> 41:03.193
That's two people

41:03.195 --> 41:06.729
who make each other
their ugliest selves.

41:08.466 --> 41:10.700
We deserve it.

41:13.270 --> 41:14.637
Why am I telling you this?

41:14.639 --> 41:17.674
Because you're finally done.
- What?

41:17.676 --> 41:18.775
Let's go.
- What?

41:18.777 --> 41:20.510
Right now.
Let's get out of here.

41:20.512 --> 41:22.212
Well, we can't just leave.

41:22.214 --> 41:23.546
That's exactly
what we need to do.

41:23.548 --> 41:26.216
We might be trapped,
but we're not handcuffed.

41:26.218 --> 41:27.383
Let's go.
- Oh, my God. Can we?

41:27.385 --> 41:30.420
They'll be back soon,
and we'll be gone.

41:30.422 --> 41:31.521
Okay.
Holy shit.

41:31.523 --> 41:34.224
Do you have a car?
- Yes.

41:34.226 --> 41:35.291
Go upstairs to your room,

41:35.293 --> 41:36.693
grab only
- What you absolutely need,

41:36.695 --> 41:39.829
and meet me where we smoked
last night, okay?

41:39.831 --> 41:41.531
Okay.
- Don't run.

41:41.533 --> 41:43.600
Okay.

41:56.847 --> 42:01.484
[ Rattling ]

42:01.486 --> 42:03.219
Oh, my God, Robin.
- What?

42:03.221 --> 42:07.257
You said grab...
Come on. Let's go.

42:07.259 --> 42:08.758
Do you have your own key
to the car?

42:08.760 --> 42:10.693
I can't believe
we're doing this.

42:10.695 --> 42:13.530
Do you have your own key?

42:15.666 --> 42:17.600
Yes.
It's in my purse.

42:17.602 --> 42:19.869
It's right this way.
It's the...

42:19.871 --> 42:21.871
It's the Tesla.
- Unlock it.

42:21.873 --> 42:23.873
Unlock it!
No. It opens automatically

42:23.875 --> 42:25.675
when you walk up to it,
it just knows.

42:25.677 --> 42:27.277
How does it know
to pop the trunk?

42:27.279 --> 42:29.746
I think you have to press
a button on the key.

42:29.748 --> 42:31.347
Then pull out the key.

42:31.349 --> 42:32.215
Shit.

42:32.217 --> 42:34.617
Oh, all this stupid
shit in here!

42:34.619 --> 42:36.586
I can't see!

42:39.390 --> 42:40.490
Ha! Found it!

42:40.492 --> 42:43.493
Keep your voice down.
- What is it?

42:44.862 --> 42:47.497
Who is that?
- Wait, Robin.

42:47.499 --> 42:51.267
Who is that?
Bill?

42:51.269 --> 42:52.402
Robin, wait.

42:52.404 --> 42:53.836
Bill?
- Wait.

42:53.838 --> 42:55.371
Robin.

42:55.373 --> 42:57.574
No, no, no, no.

43:03.414 --> 43:05.748
Oh, my God.

43:05.750 --> 43:08.484
Oh, my God.

43:08.486 --> 43:10.753
Ahh!

43:24.969 --> 43:28.538
[ Sobs, gags ]

43:28.540 --> 43:29.672
Do not throw up.

43:29.674 --> 43:32.875
Do not put your DNA
all over the parking lot.

43:32.877 --> 43:35.511
I didn't see anything!
I won't tell anyone!

43:35.513 --> 43:36.613
Stop! Stop!
I promise! No!

43:36.615 --> 43:38.615
Just let me go!
Shh. Stop. Stop.

43:38.617 --> 43:41.250
Stop. Stop.
Stop. Stop.

43:41.252 --> 43:43.486
I told you not to run, okay?

43:43.488 --> 43:44.854
Don't answer me.
Don't cry.

43:44.856 --> 43:47.724
Don't shout.
Don't scream, okay?

43:47.726 --> 43:53.930
Okay. I am not going
to kill you, okay?

43:53.932 --> 43:55.698
Okay.
- Okay.

43:55.700 --> 43:57.800
I didn't tell anyone.

43:57.802 --> 43:59.469
You still haven't, okay?

43:59.471 --> 44:01.638
Okay.
- Okay?

44:01.640 --> 44:03.373
Is she dead?
- Yes, she is dead.

44:03.375 --> 44:06.809
Stay...
Don't you move.

44:13.517 --> 44:16.919
We have to put the bodies
in the trunk, okay?

44:16.921 --> 44:18.888
I'm...
We're taking their car?

44:18.890 --> 44:21.891
They're no longer
staying at this hotel.

44:34.972 --> 44:36.673
Let's go back inside.

44:36.675 --> 44:37.640
What?

44:37.642 --> 44:39.375
We have to get our things.

44:39.377 --> 44:40.910
I have my things.

44:40.912 --> 44:41.811
I have to get my things.

44:41.813 --> 44:44.647
And we have to check out like
normal people in the morning.

44:44.649 --> 44:46.949
What? No.
I can't stay there.

44:46.951 --> 44:48.785
I can't.

44:48.787 --> 44:50.787
I'm telling you what to do
if you don't want to

44:50.789 --> 44:53.756
go back to prison
for the rest of your life.

44:53.758 --> 44:55.458
Okay?
- Okay.

44:55.460 --> 44:57.493
When the police
start asking questions,

44:57.495 --> 44:58.995
they will have
a very clear timeline

44:58.997 --> 45:00.530
of when Robin
and Bill were last seen,

45:00.532 --> 45:03.599
which cannot be the same time
you and I were last seen.

45:03.601 --> 45:06.069
Do you understand?

45:06.071 --> 45:07.603
Yeah.

45:07.605 --> 45:08.871
Okay.

45:08.873 --> 45:11.541
We put them
out of their misery.

45:13.010 --> 45:15.445
Don't you think?

45:24.855 --> 45:28.257
Who puts us out of our misery?

45:33.630 --> 45:36.733
Would you like something
to help you sleep?

45:41.071 --> 45:43.272
Yes.

45:50.547 --> 45:53.416
[ Safe chiming ]

46:44.868 --> 46:48.971
You're all set, sir.

46:48.973 --> 46:51.774
Thank you, sir.

46:51.776 --> 46:52.675
[ Engine starts ]

46:52.677 --> 46:56.112
We're just gonna leave them
in the parking lot?

46:56.114 --> 46:58.314
No.

47:18.202 --> 47:20.870
Javier:
They're over there.

47:21.638 --> 47:25.007
Letty: You walked all the way
back to the hotel from here?

47:25.009 --> 47:30.713
Yeah. It was an hour,
maybe a little more.

47:30.715 --> 47:31.981
Now what?

47:31.983 --> 47:32.915
We have two cars.

47:32.917 --> 47:35.751
This one is due back to
the airport in Knoxville, hmm?

47:35.753 --> 47:37.787
I'll take this one.

47:37.789 --> 47:40.456
No, no, no, no.

47:40.458 --> 47:42.625
I'll drive this one.

47:42.627 --> 47:44.927
You drive that one.

47:47.965 --> 47:49.532
Follow me.

47:51.668 --> 47:55.771
Letty, use your turn
signals, okay?

47:55.773 --> 47:57.940
Every time.

48:54.932 --> 48:57.199
[ Dinging ]

48:57.201 --> 49:01.103
[ Scanning through
radio stations ]

49:01.105 --> 49:04.507
